# Tailwind CSS Patterns

## Class Organization

Order classes consistently for readability:

1. Layout (display, position, flex/grid)
2. Sizing (width, height, padding, margin)
3. Typography (font, text)
4. Visual (background, border, shadow)
5. Interactive (hover, focus, transition)

```tsx
// GOOD - organized classes
<button className="
  flex items-center justify-center
  px-4 py-2 w-full
  text-sm font-medium text-white
  bg-primary rounded-lg shadow-sm
  hover:bg-primary-dark focus:outline-none focus:ring-2
  transition-colors duration-200
">
  Click Me
</button>
```

## Design Tokens via CSS Variables

Use CSS variables for theming instead of hardcoded values:

```css
/* globals.css */
:root {
  --color-primary: #1C8841;
  --color-primary-dark: #166b34;
  --color-background: #ffffff;
  --color-text: #1f2937;
  
  --spacing-1: 0.25rem;
  --spacing-2: 0.5rem;
  --spacing-4: 1rem;
  
  --duration-fast: 150ms;
  --duration-normal: 200ms;
  --duration-slow: 300ms;
}

.dark {
  --color-background: #111827;
  --color-text: #f9fafb;
}
```

```tsx
// Use in components
<div className="bg-[var(--color-primary)] text-[var(--color-text)]">
  Content
</div>

// Or extend Tailwind config
// tailwind.config.js
module.exports = {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        primary: 'var(--color-primary)',
        'primary-dark': 'var(--color-primary-dark)',
      },
    },
  },
};
```

